:::summary
Natural law is the philosophical and theological doctrine that there exists a universal moral order — discoverable by human reason — that stands above all human law and provides the standard by which all positive law is to be judged. Rooted in ancient Greek philosophy and developed to its greatest heights by [Thomas Aquinas](article.html?id=aquinas), natural law has been the philosophical backbone of Western jurisprudence, Christian moral theology, and the American founding — the basis on which [Thomas Jefferson](article.html?id=thomas-jefferson) could assert that certain rights are not granted by government but endowed by the Creator.
:::

